01:25:07.030 --> 01:25:08.970
Worm?

01:25:11.040 --> 01:25:13.470
Hey, Les.

01:25:13.540 --> 01:25:15.470
Hey.

01:25:15.540 --> 01:25:18.100
Hey, you all right?

01:25:18.180 --> 01:25:20.110
Mike?

01:25:20.180 --> 01:25:22.110
Yeah.

01:25:23.680 --> 01:25:26.120
You should've played
those kings, Mike.

01:25:26.180 --> 01:25:29.020
Aw, you're an asshole.

01:25:29.090 --> 01:25:32.990
I know. I know.
I'm sorry.

01:25:34.560 --> 01:25:36.650
They took
every fucking nickel.

01:25:36.730 --> 01:25:40.320
I think I got 300
in my boot somewhere.

01:25:42.400 --> 01:25:45.030
Oh, look at you.
Fuck!

01:25:45.100 --> 01:25:47.970
Fuck, I cannot believe
I caught a hanger.

01:25:48.040 --> 01:25:52.840
- Aw, it's never happened, I swear to God.
- Where's the car?

01:25:52.910 --> 01:25:56.110
- God, I think I cracked a rib.
- What the fuck were you thinking?

01:25:56.180 --> 01:25:59.340
- I was trying to give us an edge.
- I had 'em.

01:25:59.420 --> 01:26:01.890
Hey, I'm sorry
we got banged up, all right?

01:26:01.950 --> 01:26:04.390
I took a shot and I missed.
That happens.

01:26:04.460 --> 01:26:08.120
- Fucking happens all the time around you.
- What, it doesn't happen to you?

01:26:08.190 --> 01:26:11.390
You're the guy who flushed his whole
fucking bankroll on one hand, Mike.

01:26:11.460 --> 01:26:13.716
Oh, hey, fuck you,
man. That was different.

01:26:14.016 --> 01:26:15.400
Why? Explain that to me.

01:26:15.470 --> 01:26:18.560
Why different, huh?
What makes you so fucking special?

01:26:18.640 --> 01:26:20.930
How come all your moves
are so smart and noble...

01:26:21.010 --> 01:26:23.370
and I'm always
the idiot piece of shit?

01:26:23.440 --> 01:26:26.170
You act like you're the only one
with any fucking ambition.

01:26:26.240 --> 01:26:29.800
What's your ambition, man? Tell me.
I don't know. What is it?

01:26:29.880 --> 01:26:32.133
I don't even know. I
don't think like that.

01:26:32.433 --> 01:26:33.610
No, you don't think.

01:26:33.680 --> 01:26:35.620
No, I don't think
like you!

01:26:35.690 --> 01:26:38.620
You always think you can beat the game
straight up. That's not me.

01:26:38.690 --> 01:26:40.592
I told you, I'm always gonna
look for that edge. Always.

01:26:40.892 --> 01:26:41.660
What's the edge now?

01:26:41.730 --> 01:26:44.160
We owe 15 grand in a day.
What do we do?

01:26:44.230 --> 01:26:47.060
It's easy. We get
the fuck outta Dodge, all right?

01:26:47.130 --> 01:26:49.960
We just steer clear
of the city for a while.

01:26:50.030 --> 01:26:53.370
We'll hit the road. We'll be up again
in no time. This'll all blow over.

01:26:53.440 --> 01:26:54.073
We'll have a ball.

01:26:54.373 --> 01:26:56.130
Not a fucking chance
I'm gonna live like that.

01:26:56.210 --> 01:26:58.898
You talk to Grama.
You get him to stake me.

01:26:59.198 --> 01:27:00.970
It's not gonna work, okay?

01:27:01.050 --> 01:27:03.640
We're not dealing with Grama.

01:27:05.220 --> 01:27:08.310
You said
Grama's on his own.

01:27:08.390 --> 01:27:12.120
- You told me Grama's on his own.
- KGB bankrolled him.

01:27:13.820 --> 01:27:18.390
- So you've just fucked us right in the ass.
- Yeah, all the way, okay?

01:27:18.460 --> 01:27:22.490
So you see what I'm saying?
No fooling around. It's highway time.

01:27:22.570 --> 01:27:25.970
Are you with me or not?

01:27:26.040 --> 01:27:28.330
No, I'm not this time.

01:27:35.510 --> 01:27:39.510
- Give me the keys.
- You're really gonna go back there?

01:27:40.580 --> 01:27:42.880
Yeah.

01:27:44.150 --> 01:27:47.120
I'll see you
when I see you.

01:27:49.160 --> 01:27:53.030
Hey. At least you're
rounding again, right?

01:27:53.100 --> 01:27:56.460
You're gonna thank me
for that someday.

01:28:06.980 --> 01:28:11.010
Fold or hang tough.
Call or raise the bet.

01:28:11.080 --> 01:28:14.180
These are decisions
you make at the table.

01:28:14.250 --> 01:28:17.780
Sometimes the odds are stacked so clear,
there's only one way to play it.

01:28:17.860 --> 01:28:21.920
Other times, like holding a small pair
against two over cards,

01:28:21.990 --> 01:28:24.620
it's six to five,
or even money, either way.

01:28:24.700 --> 01:28:28.260
Then it's all about feel,
what's in your guts.

01:28:29.330 --> 01:28:31.300
Well, look at you.

01:28:31.370 --> 01:28:33.670
Look at me.

01:28:33.740 --> 01:28:35.760
Come in.

01:28:35.840 --> 01:28:37.770
No.

01:28:37.840 --> 01:28:42.300
- Where's your friend?
- Uh, he's gone.

01:28:42.380 --> 01:28:46.320
- He's gone.
- So you brought my money?

01:28:47.890 --> 01:28:51.950
- I'm a little short.
- How short?

01:28:52.020 --> 01:28:53.790
The whole way.

01:28:53.860 --> 01:28:56.920
There must be
some kind of story.

01:28:58.660 --> 01:29:00.690
Well...

01:29:00.760 --> 01:29:04.260
as you can see,
I can't pay you.

01:29:04.340 --> 01:29:07.100
I see you're
banged up pretty good.

01:29:11.440 --> 01:29:14.610
You never should've vouched
for that scumbag.

01:29:17.750 --> 01:29:19.680
Maybe not.

01:29:21.250 --> 01:29:24.650
- You're leaving me no outs here.
- Why?

01:29:24.720 --> 01:29:28.280
I can't trust you two
aren't playing me.

01:29:28.360 --> 01:29:30.850
I'm not the one
working with a partner here.

01:29:32.930 --> 01:29:37.200
You wanna take it up with KGB,
you go right ahead.

01:29:37.270 --> 01:29:42.800
Otherwise, you got one day,
or this'll feel like a Swedish massage.

01:30:00.160 --> 01:30:02.250
- Hey.
- Hey, what's up?

01:30:12.800 --> 01:30:16.570
You look like Duane Bobick
after one round with Norton.

01:30:16.640 --> 01:30:21.580
- What the fuck happened to you?
- Ah, Worm.

01:30:22.650 --> 01:30:24.880
When are you
gonna listen?

01:30:24.950 --> 01:30:27.420
I'm listening.

01:30:27.480 --> 01:30:31.280
What do you need?
500? A grand?

01:30:31.360 --> 01:30:33.950
- Huh?
- I need-- I need 15,000.

01:30:34.020 --> 01:30:36.580
- Fifteen?
- Yep.

01:30:36.660 --> 01:30:39.750
I need a blow job
from Christy Turlington.

01:30:39.830 --> 01:30:43.430
- Get the fuck outta here. $15,000?
- Seriously, Joey.

01:30:43.500 --> 01:30:47.440
What can you do for me? Five hundred
dollars is not even gonna get me started.

01:30:47.500 --> 01:30:52.310
Goddamn it, Mike, if 500 won't
help, what's two grand gonna do?

01:30:53.880 --> 01:30:56.440
What kind of trouble
you in?

01:30:56.510 --> 01:30:59.570
I'm in the worst kind,
with the worst guy.

01:30:59.650 --> 01:31:01.740
- KGB?
- Yep.

01:31:03.820 --> 01:31:05.760
Come here.

01:31:07.320 --> 01:31:09.590
Didn't I tell you...

01:31:09.660 --> 01:31:12.560
to never let that guy
get a hold of you?

01:31:12.630 --> 01:31:16.000
- You told me a lot of things.
- Yeah, yeah. And you don't listen.

01:31:16.070 --> 01:31:19.000
I tell you to play within your means,
you risk your whole bankroll.

01:31:19.070 --> 01:31:21.560
I tell you not to
overextend yourself, to rebuild,

01:31:21.640 --> 01:31:24.040
you go into hock for more.

01:31:24.110 --> 01:31:26.670
I was giving you
a living, Mike,

01:31:26.740 --> 01:31:30.180
showing you the playbook
I put together off my own beats.

01:31:30.250 --> 01:31:32.180
That wasn't enough
for you--

01:31:32.250 --> 01:31:36.120
This is one time I don't need
you to tell me how I fucked up.

01:31:36.190 --> 01:31:38.120
I know I fucked up.

01:31:38.190 --> 01:31:41.160
What I need from you
is money.

01:31:41.230 --> 01:31:44.130
- I need whatever money you can give me.
- See, that's the thing.

01:31:44.190 --> 01:31:46.790
This time
there is no money.

01:31:46.860 --> 01:31:50.360
I give you two grand,
what's that buy you? A day?

01:31:50.430 --> 01:31:52.630
No, I give it to you,
I'm wasting it.

01:31:52.700 --> 01:31:55.470
- That's fucking great.
- You did it to yourself.

01:31:55.540 --> 01:31:58.470
You had to put it all on the line
for some Vegas pipe dream.

01:31:58.540 --> 01:32:00.570
Yeah, I took a risk.
I took a risk.

01:32:00.640 --> 01:32:03.140
You see all the angles.
You never have the stones to play one.

01:32:03.210 --> 01:32:07.010
"Stones"?
You little punk.

01:32:07.080 --> 01:32:09.920
I'm not playing for the thrill
of fucking victory here.

01:32:09.990 --> 01:32:15.250
I owe rent, alimony, child support.
I play for money.

01:32:15.330 --> 01:32:17.260
My kids eat.

01:32:17.330 --> 01:32:19.800
I got stones enough
not to chase cards, action...

01:32:19.860 --> 01:32:23.660
or fucking pipe dreams
of winning the World Series on ESPN.

01:32:23.730 --> 01:32:26.360
You want me to, uh,
call some people,

01:32:26.440 --> 01:32:28.600
try and buy you
some time, I will.

01:32:28.670 --> 01:32:31.160
Place to stay, or the truck.
No problem.

01:32:31.240 --> 01:32:35.610
But about the money,
I gotta do this. I gotta say no.

01:32:35.680 --> 01:32:39.270
That's fine.
I understand.

01:32:42.490 --> 01:32:45.080
- Hey, listen.
- What?

01:32:45.160 --> 01:32:47.750
I put it all on the line.
That's true.

01:32:47.830 --> 01:32:51.490
And you know what?
It wasn't a bad beat.

01:32:51.560 --> 01:32:53.550
I wasn't unlucky.

01:32:53.630 --> 01:32:56.460
I got outplayed.
I got outplayed that time.

01:32:58.040 --> 01:33:01.060
But I know I'm good enough
to sit at that table.

01:33:01.140 --> 01:33:03.610
It's not-- It's not
a fucking pipe dream.

01:33:03.670 --> 01:33:06.140
I don't doubt your talent.

01:33:06.210 --> 01:33:09.240
I never--
I never told anybody this.

01:33:09.310 --> 01:33:13.410
About eight, nine months ago,
I'm at the Taj, it's late,

01:33:13.480 --> 01:33:15.510
and I see Johnny Chan
walk in.

01:33:15.590 --> 01:33:17.520
And he goes,
he sits 300-600.

01:33:17.590 --> 01:33:20.420
And the whole place stops
when Johnny Chan walks in.

01:33:20.490 --> 01:33:22.580
Everybody puts
an eye on him.

01:33:22.660 --> 01:33:25.090
After a little while,
there wasn't a crap game going...

01:33:25.160 --> 01:33:27.600
'cause all the high rollers
are over there watching him.

01:33:27.660 --> 01:33:30.500
Some are playing with him, giving
away their money to this guy to say...

01:33:30.570 --> 01:33:32.500
"Oh, I played
with the World Champion."

01:33:32.570 --> 01:33:35.500
And you know what I did?
I sat down.

01:33:35.570 --> 01:33:39.270
Nah, you need 50, 60 grand
to play right in that game.

01:33:39.340 --> 01:33:41.830
Well, I had six,
but I had to know.

01:33:41.910 --> 01:33:43.850
What happened?

01:33:43.910 --> 01:33:47.180
Played tight for an hour. I folded
mostly, and then I made a score.

01:33:47.250 --> 01:33:50.620
- Wired aces or kings?
- Rags.

01:33:51.920 --> 01:33:55.410
I had nothing.
But he raised.

01:33:55.490 --> 01:33:58.090
And I just decided, you know,
I don't care about the money.

01:33:58.160 --> 01:34:00.430
I'm just gonna
outplay the guy.

01:34:00.500 --> 01:34:03.160
I'm just gonna outplay
this guy this hand.

01:34:03.230 --> 01:34:05.930
- I re-raised.
- Re-raise.

01:34:06.000 --> 01:34:08.770
- You played right back at him, huh?
- Oh, yeah.

01:34:08.840 --> 01:34:11.330
And he just comes right
back over the top of me,

01:34:11.410 --> 01:34:13.930
trying to bully me like
I'm some fucking tourist.

01:34:14.010 --> 01:34:15.950
I hesitate for two seconds.
I re-raised.

01:34:16.010 --> 01:34:18.980
And he makes a move toward his checks,
and he looks at me.

01:34:19.050 --> 01:34:22.490
And he looks at his cards,
and he looks at me again.

01:34:22.550 --> 01:34:25.780
And he mucked it.
I took it down.

01:34:25.860 --> 01:34:30.730
"Did you have it?"
"I'm sorry, John. I don't remember."

01:34:32.560 --> 01:34:35.400
I got up, and I walked
to the cashier.

01:34:35.470 --> 01:34:39.030
I sat with the best
in the world, and I won.

01:34:39.100 --> 01:34:42.970
You put a fucking move on Chan,
you son of a bitch.

01:34:43.040 --> 01:34:46.170
So that's why you made
that run on KGB's place.

01:34:46.240 --> 01:34:48.680
That's right.

01:34:48.750 --> 01:34:51.410
And I'll do it again
if I can.

01:34:53.080 --> 01:34:55.520
Well, then I'm rooting
for you, Mike.

01:34:56.590 --> 01:34:58.550
I'll see you around,
Knish.

01:35:00.090 --> 01:35:04.120
This is temporary?
Will you be back next semester?

01:35:04.190 --> 01:35:07.430
Oh, I think we
both know I'm no lawyer.

01:35:08.600 --> 01:35:11.470
I hope my story
didn't discourage you.

01:35:11.540 --> 01:35:16.560
No. It inspired me.
I think I was on my way out anyway.

01:35:16.640 --> 01:35:19.670
- But now you're here.
- That's right.

01:35:19.740 --> 01:35:23.340
- You're in trouble?
- Yes, sir, I am.

01:35:23.410 --> 01:35:28.250
Uh, not with the law.
I owe.

01:35:28.320 --> 01:35:32.190
- A gambling debt?
- Yeah.

01:35:32.260 --> 01:35:37.250
It's not mine. It's, uh--
I vouched for the wrong guy.

01:35:37.330 --> 01:35:40.090
Um, so now it's on me.

01:35:40.160 --> 01:35:42.100
I understand.

01:35:44.170 --> 01:35:47.190
So, what will it take
for you to be free of this?

01:35:49.370 --> 01:35:52.540
- I need 15,000 tonight.
- Michael!

01:35:52.610 --> 01:35:55.370
Michael!

01:35:59.320 --> 01:36:02.380
- You know, I'm not a wealthy man, Michael.
- I know.

01:36:02.450 --> 01:36:05.850
And it kills me
to ask you, but...

01:36:05.920 --> 01:36:08.720
I don't have
any other play here.

01:36:08.790 --> 01:36:11.960
So, uh, if you can
help me at all--

01:36:12.030 --> 01:36:14.090
I hate to see you
like this.

01:36:14.160 --> 01:36:16.600
I want to help you, Michael.
But $15,000, I-- I--

01:36:16.670 --> 01:36:18.530
I know.

01:36:25.240 --> 01:36:27.300
If it must be tonight,

01:36:28.880 --> 01:36:31.910
then ten
is the best I can do.

01:36:33.480 --> 01:36:35.580
Would you do that?

01:36:40.060 --> 01:36:43.150
When my mother
let me leave the yeshiva,

01:36:43.230 --> 01:36:45.990
it nearly broke her.

01:36:46.060 --> 01:36:50.300
But she knew--
She knew the life I had to lead.

01:36:52.370 --> 01:36:55.130
To do that for another
is a mitzvah.

01:36:58.010 --> 01:37:01.410
And for that, I owe.

01:37:15.560 --> 01:37:19.190
So you take this money...

01:37:19.260 --> 01:37:22.230
and you get yourself
out of this trouble.

01:37:22.300 --> 01:37:24.230
You hear me?

01:37:29.340 --> 01:37:31.670
I know you can.

01:37:34.340 --> 01:37:38.680
I-- I promise that I'm gonna--
I'll pay you back.

01:37:39.750 --> 01:37:41.680
Good luck.

01:38:03.810 --> 01:38:07.640
I've often seen these people,
these squares, at the table.

01:38:07.710 --> 01:38:11.880
Short-stacked and long odds against,
all their outs gone,

01:38:11.950 --> 01:38:14.640
one last card in the deck
that can help them.

01:38:16.350 --> 01:38:20.720
I used to wonder how they could let
themselves get into such bad shape...

01:38:20.790 --> 01:38:23.990
and how the hell they thought
they could turn it around.

01:38:31.000 --> 01:38:33.490
Just walking in here
makes me queasy.

01:38:33.570 --> 01:38:36.700
The brick walls.
The fucking mopes at the tables.

01:38:36.770 --> 01:38:40.970
The musty smell. I feel like Buckner
walking back into Shea.

01:38:41.040 --> 01:38:43.540
But what choice do I have?

01:38:43.610 --> 01:38:46.450
So, you have my money?

01:38:46.520 --> 01:38:49.420
- I owe you that money tomorrow, right?
- Da.

01:38:50.990 --> 01:38:53.110
So it's still mine.

01:38:53.190 --> 01:38:58.220
For the next eight hours,
it is yours.

01:38:58.300 --> 01:39:01.630
But if you
don't have it all by then,

01:39:01.700 --> 01:39:04.460
then you are mine.

01:39:04.530 --> 01:39:06.470
Well...

01:39:11.440 --> 01:39:16.110
I got $10,000.
I'm looking for a game.

01:39:17.310 --> 01:39:20.440
- You sure?
- You heard me.

01:39:24.050 --> 01:39:27.250
So, we'll play. Heads up.

01:39:27.320 --> 01:39:30.520
We both start
with a couple of racks.

01:39:30.590 --> 01:39:34.330
Blinds, uh, 25 and 50?

01:39:34.400 --> 01:39:39.060
And we don't stop
until one of us has it all.

01:39:41.140 --> 01:39:44.000
Let's do it.

01:40:08.870 --> 01:40:11.660
I'm gonna raise.

01:40:11.740 --> 01:40:13.790
Thousand straight.

01:40:13.870 --> 01:40:16.360
Very aggressive.

01:40:16.440 --> 01:40:19.170
A new day.

01:40:19.240 --> 01:40:23.040
And you won't be pushed around.

01:40:23.110 --> 01:40:26.840
But... I re-raise.

01:40:26.920 --> 01:40:30.720
Five thousand.

01:40:32.790 --> 01:40:35.660
Doyle Brunson says,
"The key to No-Limit...

01:40:35.730 --> 01:40:38.460
is to put a man to a decision
for all his chips."

01:40:38.530 --> 01:40:40.460
Teddy's just done it.

01:40:40.530 --> 01:40:43.690
He's representing aces,
the only hand better than my cowboys.

01:40:43.770 --> 01:40:46.500
I can't call and give him
a chance to catch.

01:40:46.570 --> 01:40:49.660
I can only fold,
if I believe him. Or--

01:40:49.740 --> 01:40:52.140
I re-raise. I'm all in.

01:41:22.740 --> 01:41:24.830
Take it down.

01:41:32.780 --> 01:41:34.720
In a heads-up match,

01:41:34.780 --> 01:41:38.950
the size of your stack is almost as
important as the quality of your cards.

01:41:39.020 --> 01:41:41.620
I chopped one of his legs out
in the first hand.

01:41:41.690 --> 01:41:45.145
Now all I have to do is lean
on him until he falls over.

01:41:45.445 --> 01:41:45.990
Check.

01:41:46.060 --> 01:41:48.530
Bet a thousand.

01:41:48.600 --> 01:41:51.620
Call. I'll call.

01:41:55.510 --> 01:41:57.100
Check.

01:41:58.680 --> 01:42:02.300
What's that, 2,500 there?
I'm gonna tap your tap.

01:42:11.990 --> 01:42:13.460
Jacks up.

01:42:15.890 --> 01:42:17.830
Very good.

01:42:19.530 --> 01:42:21.830
Good hand.

01:42:21.900 --> 01:42:26.300
Catching that Jack
on the turn.

01:42:26.370 --> 01:42:31.000
- You got lucky there.
- Yep, it was luck.

01:42:31.070 --> 01:42:35.070
So, that's it then, hmm?

01:42:35.150 --> 01:42:40.170
Just like a young man
coming in for a quickie.

01:42:40.250 --> 01:42:45.020
I feel so unsatisfied.

01:42:45.090 --> 01:42:47.020
I'm sorry.

01:42:47.090 --> 01:42:50.820
You must feel proud
and good.

01:42:50.890 --> 01:42:53.990
Strong enough
to beat the world.

01:42:55.570 --> 01:43:00.230
- I feel fine.
- Me too. I feel okay.

01:43:01.740 --> 01:43:05.270
'Course maybe we check
with one other guy, see how he feels.

01:43:05.340 --> 01:43:07.940
Grama!

01:43:10.850 --> 01:43:13.280
I thought I smelled him.

01:43:13.350 --> 01:43:15.720
I'll take what's ours.

01:43:15.790 --> 01:43:18.650
'Course you could
let it ride, Mike.

01:43:18.720 --> 01:43:21.780
Take your chances.
You could let this happen, Grama?

01:43:21.860 --> 01:43:23.880
Sure, partner.

01:43:23.960 --> 01:43:27.160
He still has till morning
to make good.

01:43:27.230 --> 01:43:32.690
Uh, you know what? I got my
five grand here. That's just fine by me.

01:43:32.770 --> 01:43:36.000
- I'm going home.
- Fine.

01:43:36.070 --> 01:43:38.400
It's a fucking joke anyway.

01:43:38.480 --> 01:43:43.140
After all, I am paying you
with your money.

01:43:46.050 --> 01:43:49.450
- What did you say?
- Your money.

01:43:49.520 --> 01:43:52.960
I am still up 20 grand...

01:43:53.020 --> 01:43:56.580
from this last time
I stick it in you.

01:43:56.660 --> 01:44:00.860
They're trying
to goad me, trying to own me.

01:44:00.930 --> 01:44:06.030
But this isn't a gunfight. It's not
about pride or ego. It's only about money.

01:44:06.100 --> 01:44:09.800
I can leave now,
even with Grama and KGB...

01:44:09.870 --> 01:44:13.330
and halfway
to paying Petrovsky back.

01:44:13.410 --> 01:44:15.340
That's the safe play.

01:44:15.410 --> 01:44:19.110
I told Worm you can't lose
what you don't put in the middle.

01:44:19.180 --> 01:44:23.020
- Deal 'em.
- But you can't win much either.

01:44:25.260 --> 01:44:27.280
Checks!

01:44:29.190 --> 01:44:33.150
- Double the blinds?
- Yeah.

01:44:33.230 --> 01:44:35.360
Table stakes.

01:44:35.430 --> 01:44:38.960
Good. Feel free
to reload at any time.

01:44:55.150 --> 01:44:58.680
You must
be kicking yourself...

01:44:58.760 --> 01:45:02.890
for not walking out
when you could.

01:45:04.960 --> 01:45:07.400
Bad judgment.

01:45:07.460 --> 01:45:09.660
But...

01:45:09.730 --> 01:45:12.100
don't you worry, son.

01:45:12.170 --> 01:45:16.160
It will all be over soon.

01:45:21.580 --> 01:45:23.240
Okay.

01:45:47.540 --> 01:45:49.510
Check.

01:45:51.070 --> 01:45:54.640
No check here.
I tap you.

01:46:09.460 --> 01:46:11.790
I'm laying
this down, Teddy.

01:46:13.360 --> 01:46:15.700
Top two pair.

01:46:15.770 --> 01:46:19.260
It's a monster hand,
and I'm gonna lay that down...

01:46:19.340 --> 01:46:23.290
'cause you got two-four, and I'm
not gonna draw against a made hand.

01:46:28.510 --> 01:46:32.310
Lays down a monster.

01:46:38.220 --> 01:46:40.820
Should have paid me off
on that.

01:46:43.290 --> 01:46:46.820
Why the fuck did you
lay that down?

01:47:02.250 --> 01:47:05.740
Wow.
Not hungry?

01:47:05.820 --> 01:47:09.010
Mr. Son of a Bitch.

01:47:09.090 --> 01:47:12.450
Let's play some cards.

01:47:12.520 --> 01:47:14.460
The rule is this:

01:47:14.520 --> 01:47:17.820
You spot a man's tell,
you don't say a fucking word.

01:47:17.890 --> 01:47:19.830
I finally spotted KGB's.

01:47:19.900 --> 01:47:24.200
And usually I would've let him go on
chewing those Oreos till he was dead broke.

01:47:24.270 --> 01:47:29.070
But I don't have that kind of time.
I've only got till morning.

01:47:29.140 --> 01:47:33.510
Not even Teddy KGB's immune
to getting a little rattled.

01:47:33.580 --> 01:47:37.340
Enough is enough, Teddy.
Finish the fucking kid off.

01:47:37.410 --> 01:47:40.380
Hanging around.
Hanging around.

01:47:40.450 --> 01:47:45.220
Kid's got alligator blood.
Can't get rid of him.

01:47:48.360 --> 01:47:51.160
No, I'm not going anywhere.
Double the blind.

01:47:51.230 --> 01:47:53.820
Okay.

01:47:53.900 --> 01:47:55.630
I call.

01:48:04.870 --> 01:48:06.810
Check.

01:48:18.720 --> 01:48:20.950
Two grand.

01:48:24.430 --> 01:48:26.690
All right, I'll call the two grand.
I'll gamble.

01:48:26.760 --> 01:48:29.160
Don't splash the pot.

01:48:30.270 --> 01:48:34.200
You're on a draw, Mike?
Go away.

01:48:34.270 --> 01:48:36.600
This one
is not good for you.

01:48:36.670 --> 01:48:42.110
And in my club, I will splash the pot
whenever the fuck I please.

01:48:42.180 --> 01:48:44.270
Okay.

01:48:52.120 --> 01:48:54.110
I'm gonna check, Teddy.

01:48:55.690 --> 01:48:57.630
That's right.

01:48:57.690 --> 01:49:02.130
Big daddy...

01:49:02.200 --> 01:49:05.030
bets...

01:49:05.100 --> 01:49:07.570
the pot.

01:49:11.370 --> 01:49:13.310
That's 4,400.

01:49:13.380 --> 01:49:16.740
All right, I'm gonna call you, or else
I won't respect myself tomorrow morning.

01:49:16.810 --> 01:49:20.510
Respect is all you'll have left
in the morning.

01:49:22.620 --> 01:49:26.150
Last card coming.

01:49:36.430 --> 01:49:38.590
Check.

01:49:38.670 --> 01:49:42.200
It hurts, doesn't it?

01:49:42.270 --> 01:49:46.470
You can't believe
what fell.

01:49:46.540 --> 01:49:50.030
All your dreams... dashed.

01:49:50.110 --> 01:49:54.170
Hopes down
the fucking drain.

01:49:54.250 --> 01:49:58.550
Your fate, he is sitting
right beside you.

01:49:58.620 --> 01:50:01.520
That ace could not
have helped you.

01:50:03.930 --> 01:50:08.230
I bet it all.

01:50:13.700 --> 01:50:17.300
You're right, Teddy.
The ace didn't help me.

01:50:19.540 --> 01:50:21.940
I flopped
a nut straight.

01:50:23.710 --> 01:50:27.080
Motherfucker!

01:50:27.150 --> 01:50:30.740
- Motherfucker! That is it!
- That's it?

01:50:30.820 --> 01:50:32.750
What the fuck
you talking about?

01:50:32.820 --> 01:50:35.090
- Take him down, Teddy.
- Nyet! Nyet! No more!

01:50:35.160 --> 01:50:37.490
No! Not tonight!

01:50:37.560 --> 01:50:42.290
This son of bitch,
all night he check, check, check.

01:50:42.370 --> 01:50:44.300
He trapped me!

01:50:44.370 --> 01:50:46.960
Well, you feeling
satisfied now, Teddy?

01:50:47.040 --> 01:50:50.130
'Cause I can go on
busting you up all night.

01:50:50.210 --> 01:50:52.830
Nyet! Nyet!

01:50:58.150 --> 01:51:01.740
He beat me.
Straight up.

01:51:02.820 --> 01:51:04.750
Pay him.

01:51:06.060 --> 01:51:08.750
Pay that man his money.

01:51:50.630 --> 01:51:54.160
Turned my ten grand
into just over 60.

01:51:54.240 --> 01:51:57.830
Paid 15 to Grama, six went back
to the Chesterfield.

01:51:57.910 --> 01:52:01.400
As for Worm,
well, I figure we're even.

01:52:01.480 --> 01:52:04.540
And after the ten going back
to the professor,

01:52:04.610 --> 01:52:09.450
I'm back where I started,
with three stacks of high society.

01:52:18.560 --> 01:52:20.500
Hey.

01:52:22.570 --> 01:52:27.830
- You look like hell.
- Ah, well, you should've seen me yesterday.

01:52:29.910 --> 01:52:33.140
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay. You?

01:52:34.740 --> 01:52:36.870
Now I am.

01:52:41.480 --> 01:52:43.610
So, you're
outta here, huh?

01:52:43.690 --> 01:52:49.390
Yeah, I'm-- I figure
there's nothing left for me here.

01:52:49.460 --> 01:52:53.360
Listen, um, will you
give this to Petrovsky?

01:52:53.430 --> 01:52:57.460
I... didn't want to wake him up.
It's still a little early.

01:52:57.530 --> 01:53:00.560
Can I count on you
to do that?

01:53:00.640 --> 01:53:03.700
You could always count
on me, Mike.

01:53:05.310 --> 01:53:07.240
Thanks.

01:53:07.310 --> 01:53:09.610
Take care, Jo.

01:53:11.180 --> 01:53:15.120
Hey. Call me.

01:53:16.520 --> 01:53:18.450
If you need a lawyer.

01:53:18.520 --> 01:53:21.050
I will.

01:53:21.120 --> 01:53:23.920
And I will.

01:53:42.750 --> 01:53:44.680
Kennedy Airport.

01:53:53.720 --> 01:53:57.820
- So, where you headed?
- I'm going to Vegas.

01:53:57.890 --> 01:54:00.260
- Vegas, huh?
- Yeah.

01:54:00.330 --> 01:54:02.260
Good luck, man.

01:54:02.330 --> 01:54:05.460
People insist on calling it luck.

01:54:05.530 --> 01:54:07.470
Thanks.

01:54:10.240 --> 01:54:13.870
First prize at the World Series
of Poker is a million bucks.

01:54:13.940 --> 01:54:17.380
Does it have my name on it?
I don't know.

01:54:17.450 --> 01:54:19.710
But I'm gonna find out.

